analysis.title: Global Market Outlook
analysis.content: Equities Face Tariff Headwinds Amid Hard Asset Rotation. The GMS score of 52 dictates a transition into cautious neutrality as geopolitical tail-risks crystallize through proposed global tariff mandates. While SPY and QQQ exhibit surface-level resilience, the substantial appreciation in the gold-silver complex indicates a flight toward tangible value amidst fiscal-monetary uncertainty. Credit spread compression remains fragile while crypto sentiment degradation signals systemic de-risking, necessitating a strategic pause to observe regime stabilization. [ACTION: WAIT FOR PULLBACK]
